column10:
Review written ~20 hours playtimes;
This game is fun, that said it is fun for a certain type of people, I tend to enjoy the early game most(I have trouble actually keeping large militaries)
First off you have to micromanage to be effective for longer than a few dozens of turns. You have to at least a thousand years in the future to avoid dead ends. You will at some point have to deal with long stretches of nothing to do but click the next turn button. Which WILL leave you paranoid that your enemy is pulling ahead. (On higher difficulties they are)
That said seeing a strategy work when you weren't certain it would, or looking at the 5-6 techs you have on EVERYONE can be amazing.
So if you like a game that makes you fear idling, an AI that won't give you a break, and some amazing victories, pick it up.
If you have the dosh though pick up one the later ones first;
